content:
I am doing some history digging, and EIP-7 for example
```
// Specification of EIP-7
DELEGATECALL: 0xf4, takes 6 operands: 
...
in_offset: the offset into memory of the input;
in_size: the size of the input in bytes;
...
```

In what way is client implementation determining the data type and size of the `in_offset` and `in_size`?
